   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER FOUR THE SERVICE OF THE BODY Scripture Reading: 1 Pet 2:5, 9; Rev 1:6; 5:9-10; Rom 15:16; Eph 4:11-12; Mark 16:15-16; Luke 10:2-3a, 5-6; 1 Thes 2:7; John 21:15; 1 Cor 14:1, 3-5, 12, 23a, 24-25, 31; 1 Pet 2:2; Rom 12:1; Col 1:28-29.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>OUTLINE The service of the Body being the service of the New Testament priests 1 Pet 2:5, 9; Rev 1:6; 5:9-10: Being a built-up priesthood in which everyone participates and coordinates in service.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Their duty being the preaching of the gospel to save sinners, making them sacrifices for the building up of the Body of Christ, the house of God Rom 15:16; 1 Pet 2:9b, 5b; Eph 4:11-12.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>The procedure in the service of the Body: Preaching the gospel to save sinners Mark 16:15-16; Luke 10:2-3a, 5-6.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Feeding the lambs as a nursing mother 1 Thes 2:7; John 21:15.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Perfecting the saints for the building up of the Body of Christ Eph 4:11-12.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Prophesying for the Lord for the building up of the church 1 Cor 14:1, 3-5, 12, 23a, 24-25, 31.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The three steps of offering by the priests of the gospel in the church service: Preaching the gospel to save sinners, offering them up as sacrifices to God 1 Pet 2:9b, 5b; Rom 15:16.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Nourishing the believers so that they may grow up in life to present themselves as sacrifices to God 1 Pet 2:2; Rom 12:1.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Laboring and struggling according to the Lord's operation which operates in us in power to warn and teach every saint in all wisdom, that we may present every one of them full grown in Christ Col 1:28-29.</S>
   </TEXT>
